Class IInsertBuilder

  • gw.api.database.IInsertBuilder

  • public class IInsertBuilder
    Inserts some values in the given table

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      int execute()
      Executes the query. If already in a transaction, the query executes in that transaction; otherwise a new transaction is created and committed when the method returns, or rolled back if the method throws an exception. The statement that is constructed will perform default behavior for the following fields (if present and not mapped):- ID (keyable beans only): using a new key from the KeyGenerator PublicID (keyable beans only): default public id prefix followed by a ':' followed by the numeric ID BeanVersion (versionable beans only): 0 CreateTime (editable beans only): current time CreateUser (editable beans only): the current user UpdateTime (editable beans only): current time UpdateUser (editable beans only): the current user Retired (retireable beans only): 0 Columns with default values that are not mapped will be inserted with their default values.
      IInsertBuilder mapColumn(IEntityPropertyInfo column, Object value)
      In the Insert statement, maps the given column to the given value
      IInsertBuilder withDescription(String descriptionForTheQuery)
      Sets a string describing the query. Useful for debugging performance issues.
      IInsertBuilder withInsertHint(boolean withInsertHint)
      Whether to append NOLOG hint in the generated SQL (Oracle only). This behavior may be turned off globally in the configuration.
      IInsertBuilder withLogSQL(boolean logSQL)
      Turns on or off SQL logging. The query is logged to the PLLoggerCategory.SERVER_DATABASE log category at the info level
